Since your VPCs are in different AWS Regions, each Region needs its own Transit Gateway, and those Transit Gateways are connected using Transit Gateway Peering.

This is a classic hub-and-spoke architecture, where the hub provides centralized connectivity and the VPCs act as spokes.

